        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 11:29PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1129 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Texhoma, or 16 miles southwest of Guymon, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Goodwell, Gruver, and Texhoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
